{# ── TRIAGE · the whole point of the hub: two columns, stated proudly. Left = Intuit's to fix
     (account/billing/subscription/login/2FA/refunds/software-bugs) with the Intuit link. Right =
     independent ProAdvisor work inside your own books. checklist in dc-card, r-2. (H2 + H3s) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qb-support-triage" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Get to the right help faster</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Two kinds of &ldquo;QuickBooks support.&rdquo;</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 32px;max-width:68ch;">Most &ldquo;QuickBooks support&rdquo; searches are really one of two jobs. Match yours to the right column &mdash; we&rsquo;d rather route you correctly than book a call that can&rsquo;t help. The account itself is Intuit&rsquo;s; the accounting inside it is ours.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      <div class="dc-card">
        <span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">Intuit&rsquo;s to fix</span>
        <h3>Contact Intuit directly for&hellip;</h3>
        <ul class="checklist" id="qb-support-intuit-list">
          <li>Intuit <strong>account</strong> problems &mdash; access, profile, company-account ownership.</li>
          <li><strong>Billing, subscriptions, renewals, and refunds</strong> &mdash; charges, plan changes, cancellations.</li>
          <li><strong>Login, password, and two-factor (2FA)</strong> resets and lockouts.</li>
          <li><strong>QuickBooks software bugs, outages, and Intuit-side error codes</strong> &mdash; the product itself misbehaving.</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin:16px 0 0;"><a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow" style="font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:var(--color-accent);">Go to Intuit support &rarr;</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="dc-card">
        <span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">An independent ProAdvisor&rsquo;s work</span>
        <h3>Talk to an independent Certified ProAdvisor for&hellip;</h3>
        <ul class="checklist" id="qb-support-proadvisor-list">
          <li><strong>File errors and cleanup</strong> &mdash; a broken or messy company file, miscategorized transactions, books behind for months.</li>
          <li><strong>Reconciliation</strong> that won&rsquo;t balance &mdash; bank/credit-card feeds, opening balances, undeposited funds.</li>
          <li><strong>Setup and migration</strong> &mdash; a correct chart of accounts, sales-tax configuration, and Desktop-to-Online or Enterprise moves without data loss.</li>
          <li><strong>Payroll inside your file and CPA-ready books</strong> &mdash; mapping, multi-state tax setup, and statements your CPA can file from.</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin:16px 0 0;"><a href="/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review" style="font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:var(--color-accent);">Get the free file review &rarr;</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

