{# ── HELP CATEGORIES (PROSE, NO DEAD LINKS) · the symptom-level help pages fan out in a later
     wave; we describe the categories here in prose so the hub reads complete without linking
     pages that don't exist yet. (H2) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qb-support-categories" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">More help, on the way</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Common QuickBooks problems we cover.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Beyond the pages above, the most common QuickBooks problems owners bring fall into a few groups, all of them work <strong>inside your own books</strong> rather than the Intuit account: <strong>reconciliation and balance problems</strong> (a register that won&rsquo;t tie out, opening-balance errors, stuck undeposited funds); <strong>data and file health</strong> (a bloated or damaged company file, duplicate transactions, list cleanup); <strong>setup and structure</strong> (a chart of accounts that fights you, classes and locations, sales-tax configuration); <strong>connections and feeds</strong> (bank and credit-card feeds that mis-match or stop syncing); and <strong>payroll inside the file</strong> (wage and tax mapping, multi-state setup, year-end forms reconciled in your books).</p>
      <p>Dedicated guides for these are being added. In the meantime, if the issue is in your file, a Certified ProAdvisor can scope it on the free file review. If the issue is the Intuit account, the subscription, your login, or a software bug, that is Intuit&rsquo;s to fix &mdash; <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">contact Intuit directly &rarr;</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

